catalog.title: IP Mac and Cheese
catalog.notes: 2c cheese, no mozzarella. 5+0

catalog.title: IP Ham & Lentil Soup
catalog.notes: Sauté chopped onion, garlic, carrots, celery. Add 1tsp thyme, paprika; pepper to taste. Deglaze, add 6c broth and 2c water. Add cubed ham (2.5lb ham steak), 1 whole bag lentils, 2 cans petite diced tomatoes, stir; 15+15. Add 4 large handfuls scissored spinach, stir to wilt. Add 1c Parmesan cheese, stir to melt. Add 1/3c heavy cream or half&half, stir.

catalog.title: IP Beef & Broccoli
catalog.notes: 2 packs Chuck steak or steak/chickenThighs. Broccoli 2+0 (or more if necessary), set aside. Season beef, sauté (cast iron if short on time), deglaze, slice thin. Optional saute onion/jarlic. Add soy sauce, brown sugar, ground ginger. PIP 4c white rice. 8+8.

catalog.title: IP Teriyaki Chicken
catalog.notes: Steam carrots and broccoli 3 minutes. 2.5c rice PIP. 10+10 min.

catalog.title: IP chicken burrito bowls DD
catalog.notes: Brown rice: 24+0 with frozen chicken cubes. Don't forget tortilla chips!

catalog.title: IP Spaghetti
catalog.notes: 1.5lb beef. Use petite diced tomatoes. Can also add diced carrots on very top. Filipino: add ~6 hot dogs with other meat. On top, add 1tbsp ketchup, 2tbsp soy sauce, 1tbsp fish sauce, 1tbsp sugar. After cooking, shredded cheddar cheese

catalog.title: Baleadas
catalog.notes: Chorizo, scrambled egg, set aside. Mixture, refried beans, avocado, cheese--> tortilla

catalog.title: One-pan chicken and veggies
catalog.notes: Potatoes in small chunks to cook at even speed with everything else.

catalog.title: SV steak
catalog.notes: Salt, pepper, garlic powder. 129°F for 1-3 hours (expensive cut) or 24 hours (cheap cut, such as top round or chuck). Cast iron high heat, grape seed oil, season steak with Montreal seasoning, pan sear 1-2 minutes per side.

catalog.title: Tuna casserole
catalog.notes: Veggies: hidden zucchini, hidden broccoli, roasted veggies

catalog.title: Pad Thai
catalog.notes: Works well with SV/IP chicken. Can substitute ramen noodles

catalog.title: Spaghetti Squash and Meatballs
catalog.notes: IP 1.5c water, trivet, two small spaghetti squashes, halved, pitted, garlic salt; 7+5, set aside (if all 4 halves don’t fit, do 3 halves now, 1 of the halves with the sauce). Dice 1 lg onion (half for meatballs, half for sauce). Meatballs: 1lb turkey, 0.5lb beef, 2 eggs, 3/4c bread crumbs, 1/2 diced onion, 1/2tbsp italian seasoning, salt, pepper. Saute, set aside. Saute onion, garlic, deglaze, add, 1 jar red sauce, 1 can tomato sauce, 1c water (rinse jar, save), stir; add meatballs, 7+5. Thicken sauce with a small can of tomate paste by removing 1/2c sauce, thicken with paste in the jar, add back to pot, mix.

catalog.title: Southwestern Quinoa Salad
catalog.notes: Better with diced chicken breast.

catalog.title: Grilled zucchini
catalog.notes: Uniform thickness. Oil, garlic salt, pepper. A few minutes per side.

catalog.title: IP mashed potatoes
catalog.notes: 2.5lb, roughly 5 spuds. 1c liquid (half milk/cream, half broth). 2tbsp butter. salt/pepper to taste. potatoes diced in large pieces. 10+10

catalog.title: Turkey Burgers
catalog.notes: Use 1.5lb turkey, omit jalapeño, mayo too spicy

catalog.title: Chicken fried rice
catalog.notes: Recipe is for single batch

catalog.title: Hidden veggie mac & cheese
catalog.notes: VEGGIE SAUCE: Make large batch of 3 hidden veggies (butternut squash, cauliflower, carrots): steam, half in blender at a time, freeze in 3c batches. DIRECTIONS: IP 1lb pasta, 2c broth, 2c water, salt, pepper, 1tbsp buffalo sauce, 3tbsp butter; 5+0. Stir in 2c shredded cheddar cheese, 3c veggie sauce, then milk/cheese/salt until desired texture/taste (salt offsets bSquash sweetness).

catalog.title: Sausage bolognese
catalog.notes: Can use tomato sauce instead of crushed & paste

catalog.title: Nick’s Jambalaya
catalog.notes: Make it less spicy

catalog.title: Chicken meatballs
catalog.notes: Can do white sauce instead of teriyaki, good with zuquinoa

catalog.title: Sausage & peppers pasta
catalog.notes: Can add milk and more tomato sauce to make it creamy

catalog.title: Fish tacos
catalog.notes: 6x tilapia filets, seasoned with Guga+cumin. Sear on medium heat in cast iron + olive oil. Mix coleslaw kit or thinly sliced cabbage with yogurt, lemon and/or lime juice, garlic salt. Avocado optional.

catalog.title: Summer potato salad
catalog.notes: Could use bacon and HB eggs

catalog.title: Hamburgers
catalog.notes: Use ring mold. Sides: fries, broccoli, potato salad.

catalog.title: Pasta salad
catalog.notes: Possible ingredients: pasta, ham, salami, pepperoni, chicken, black olives, mozzarella, bell peppers, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, parsley, Parmesan cheese, Italian dressing.

catalog.title: IP chicken thighs
catalog.notes: Remove skin, salt/pepper/garlicPowder/paprika, sauté, deglaze, 1c water, trivet, 10+5

catalog.title: Swedish meatball pasta
catalog.notes: Good with broccoli

catalog.title: Chicken fried sandwiches
catalog.notes: Chicken breast also works

catalog.title: IP meatloaf and mashed potatoes
catalog.notes: Do the full 2lbs of beef and the full 25min. Sides well with IP corn (make before).

catalog.title: Tuna Melts
catalog.notes: Don’t watch the video in the link. 1.5x recipe. Broil for 10 minutes.

catalog.title: IP honey bourbon chicken
catalog.notes: Broccoli first. PIP white rice 15+10.

catalog.title: Pulled pork sandwiches
catalog.notes: Use Dr. Pepper. Coleslaw.

catalog.title: Salmon
catalog.notes: 129° for 1 hour

catalog.title: Quesadillas
catalog.notes: Variety of fillings!

catalog.title: Egg salad
catalog.notes: IP egg loaf, mayo dijonMustard salt pepper garlic powder paprika

catalog.title: Rice surprise
catalog.notes: Sauté ground beef, set aside. Sauté onion garlic cabbage, set aside. Rice, curry, chicken broth. Or ANY meat/veggies laying around.

catalog.title: IP Pork chops with gravy
catalog.notes: Gravy packet or ranch packet, not both. Can do 6 large bone-in chops.

catalog.title: IP chicken tikka masala
catalog.notes: ~3.5lb family pack chicken, curry powder instead of garam masala. Tomato sauce will make a burn warning, so add last and don’t stir. Only add a little half&half or milk, add cornstarch slurry to thicken, make IP rice 2.5c after

catalog.title: IP turkey quinoa bowls
catalog.notes: 1.5lb turkey. 1tbsp taco seasoning. No syrup/honey. Add tomatoes after.

catalog.title: IP Teriyaki Chicken
catalog.notes: 1.5x recipe. Can cook carrots and broccoli in sauce prior to thickening. Use recipe with white rice or cook brown rice separately ahead of time.

catalog.title: Marathon Lasagna
catalog.notes: This is a double recipe, 1x to eat, 1x to freeze (instead of cook). BUY: 2 foil pans, 1 container parmesan cheese, 24oz spinach (2 bags or 5 containers), 4 lg yams, 2 boxes no-boil lasagna, 4 jars marinara, 3lbs turkey, 4 eggs, 1 bag mozz cheese, 1x 32-oz ricotta. RECIPE: peel yams, quarter, IP 10+0. Heat oil, saute garlic/turkey/oregano/fennel/redPepper/salt, add red sauce, wilt spinach. Mash yams w/ butter/salt/pepper/4eggs/ricotta. COMBINE: sauce. Noodles/sauce/potatoes/mozz. Repeat until full, add parmesan.

catalog.title: IP pot roast
catalog.notes: BUY: This is a double recipe: makes 8 servings. BUY: onion, baby carrots, 4lb potatoes, 1 can beef broth, 1 packet onion gravy/soup mix, 1 bag corn, 4lb roast. RECIPE: cut roast into large cubes, dry rub salt/pepper/onionPowder/garlicPowder. IP saute in oil. Remove, scrape bits using a little beef broth. Add garlic, then onions and the rest of beef broth. Add beef back in, cover with onion packet. Add quartered potatoes, cook 75+20. Remove potatoes & beef. Add carrots, 0+0. Meanwhile, blend mashed potatoes with butter/milk. Shred beef. When IP finishes, whisk 2+2tbsp cornstarch slurry, then add frozen corn to cool. Layer: mashed potatoes, beef, sauce!

catalog.title: Grilled chicken
catalog.notes: Family pack chicken = double recipe

catalog.title: Chicken & dumplings
catalog.notes: 1c flour, 1.5tsp baking powder, 0.5tsp salt, parsley, MIX, 1 egg, 0.5c milk, 2tbsp vegOil, MIX. Drop by spoonful into boiling chicken broth. Cover and simmer 10-12 minutes. Add chicken and veggies.

catalog.title: IP Lasagna Soup
catalog.notes: Trust the 6c of stock (or 4c stock, 2c water). Use mini bowties and pork.

catalog.title: IP chicken enchilada soup
catalog.notes: Use vitamix to blend

catalog.title: Green Chile Chicken Chowder
catalog.notes: Use 6 potatoes instead of celery root. Make a small batch of salsa verde.

catalog.title: Enchilada stuffed shells
catalog.notes: 2x beef, 1.5x shells, serve over lettuce or with salad

catalog.title: Asparagus-stuffed chicken
catalog.notes: Family pack of chicken. Butterfly, then pound really flat. 1 bundle of asparagus, plenty of provolone. Use toothpicks to secure. Pan sear, set aside. Cast iron 1.5c chicken broth + 1can condensed cream of chicken. Add chicken, cover, bake to 160 then remove so it can reach 165. Serve over 1lb pasta, i.e. linguine or thin spaghetti. Or quinoa.

catalog.title: Chipotle chicken burritos
catalog.notes: Try to buy family pack chicken with 2 breasts. Flatten, marinade, cast iron cook to 160, rest, cube, cast iron again. Serve with cilantro rice, beans, tomatoes, Greek yogurt, cheese, and lettuce/spinach.

catalog.title: Chicken coq a vin
catalog.notes: Single batch is kind of small. 1.5x batch is ideal, 2x for XL (this size: family pack chicken breast, 5lb potatoes). Not as much wine, maybe half recommended amount. Pound chicken a little for even cooking. Cook carrots in 2nd round for 2min.

catalog.title: Creamy Lemon Butter Chicken
catalog.notes: Can use chicken breasts (2-3, pound flat, cook to 160). Don’t discard fat. Use lots of spinach. Serve over quinoa.

catalog.title: Ham & Navy Bean Soup
catalog.notes: Carve full ham, freeze half. Soak beans. IP ham hock, 7c water, 5 bay leaves, diced onion, 45+15. Remove hock and bay leaves. Add beans and diced ham, 5+5. Add sliced carrots, celery, diced potatoes, petite diced tomatoes, jarlic, paprika, pepper, rosemary, 5+0. Add splash apple cider vinegar, frozen corn.

catalog.title: IP chicken fajitas
catalog.notes: Taco seasoning, garlic powder, onion powder, paprika, chili powder, cumin, olive oil - mix in IP with small family pack chicken cut in strips. Place above trivet with water. Add sliced onion + 3 peppers. 10+0. Tortilla, Greek yogurt, cheese.

catalog.title: Beef Plov
catalog.notes: Sauté cubed/seasoned beef chuck. 4tbsp butter. Lots of half sliced baby carrots, seasoned salt, pepper, paprika, cumin, coriander. Evenly top with 2.5c rice, don't stir. Push 1-2 cross-cut garlic bulbs into rice. Top with 3c hot water. 30+10.

catalog.title: IP Chicken Curry
catalog.notes: Sauté 8-9 seasoned chicken thighs (Mueller, curry, garam masala, cumin), set aside. Sauté onion, add ginger, curry powder, cayenne. Add chicken stock, deglaze, 4c total. Add soy sauce, chicken, stir. Add 1.5c rinsed rice, whole bag baby carrots, 2lb diced potatoes, tomato sauce (paste too thick = burns), don’t stir. 5+5. Add green peas.

catalog.title: IP Chicken and Rice
catalog.notes: Sauté onion, garlic, veggies (zucchini, asparagus, carrots, cabbage, etc); set aside. Season 2 large chicken breasts with salt/pepper/gPowder/paprika; brown, set aside. Deglaze with stock/water, total 3c, add 2c white rice, trivet chicken, 3+18. Cut chicken, add back in with veggies.

catalog.title: IP Tortellini Soup
catalog.notes: Sauté onion, garlic, carrots (sausage optional). Add 2 cans petite diced tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano, 2c chicken broth, stir. Add tortellini. 15+0.  Add a few ounces of heavy cream, and thicken with cornstarch slurry. Can add spinach and/or kale.

catalog.title: IP sweet and sour chicken
catalog.notes: Cook 2c brown rice, set aside. Cut onion and peppers. Either sauté and set aside or heat in IP at end. Sauce: 1/3c sugar, 1/4c apple cider vinegar, 1/4c ketchup, 1tbsp soy sauce, 1tbsp oyster sauce, 3tbsp pineapple juice, jarlic, powdered ginger. Sauce and 2 large diced chicken breasts, 3+0. Thicken with cornstarch slurry. Add veggies and pineapple chunks.

catalog.title: IP Mediterranean Salad
catalog.notes: Sauté two large seasoned (salt, pepper, garlic powder, paprika) chicken breasts, remove. Deglaze, 2c rinsed quinoa, 3c water. Trivet, chicken, rinse cutting board to IP, 3+18. Veggies: 2 yellow peppers, 2 tomatoes, 1 cucumber, diced/sliced black olives, red onion (side). Dressing: olive oil, balsamic vinaigrette, red wine vinaigrette, lemon juice, garlic,  salt, pepper, oregano, basil. Top with crumbled feta cheese.

catalog.title: Mexican Shepherds Pie
catalog.notes: Cook 1/2 bag black beans. Cook mashed potatoes. In large skillet: saute onion, jarlic, green chilis. Saute 1lb beef w/ taco seasoning. Add 1 can drained diced tomatoes. Add black beans and frozen corn. Salt/pepper to taste. Freeze half of filling. Cover with mashed potatoes and shredded cheddar cheese. Warm in oven. Serve with tortilla chips.

catalog.title: Shrimp Alfredo
catalog.notes: Boil pasta and asparagus, drain (reserve a little pasta water). Cook 1.5lb shrimp, add spinach, wilt. Add alfredo, rinse jar with pasta water and add it, then add pasta/asparagus.

catalog.title: IP beef lo mein
catalog.notes: Half-freeze beef (colder on inside, warmer on outside), season and sauté, set aside. Saute garlic (onion optional), deglaze. Add 3tbsp brown sugar, 1/4c soy sauce, ginger powder, fish sauce; stir. Slice beef (add back in), 5+5. Add 4 packs ramen, no seasoning. 4-5 broccoli crowns, no carrots. 3+0 (slow/intermittent pressure release). Add sesame seeds.

catalog.title: IP sausage potatoes green beans
catalog.notes: Brown 1lb sausage spiral, slowly deglaze with 1c chicken broth. 2lb diced potatoes, medallion sausage, 2 packs green beans. Salt, pepper, garlic powder, Cajun seasoning, stir. 4tbsp butter in small chunks on top. 4+0.

catalog.title: Ham Cheese Potato Broccoli Soup
catalog.notes: 2/3 bag of potatoes, 2c stock, butter, salt, pepper, garlic powder, 5+10, transfer half potatoes + liquid to blender, hand mash the rest, set aside. 6 heads broccoli, 1c stock, 2+0, blend half, set aside half to chop. Sauté butter, onions, garlic, carrots, set aside. Roux butter,  1/4c flour, milk, all ingredients + half of cooked ham, diced. Add shredded cheddar plus water to desired consistency. Makes 3 batches.

catalog.title: Butternut Squash Chicken Curry
catalog.notes: Large butternut squash quartered, 10+0, set aside, mash. 3lb boneless chicken thighs, 2x 14-ounce can diced tomatoes, 1x 14-ounce can light coconut milk, 1 sweet onion diced, 3 garlic cloves diced, 1.5tbsp curry powder, 2 teaspoon ground ginger, 1 teaspoon ground coriander (optional), 2 teaspoon ground cumin, 2 teaspoon garam masala, 1 tbsp turmeric, 1/2 teaspoon freshly ground black pepper, 2 teaspoon sea salt, 13+0. Remove/chop/add chicken. 4 handfuls fresh spinach, wilt, 1.5 cup cup frozen peas, 1 bunch fresh cilantro chopped, butternut squash. Can serve over rice!

catalog.title: IP bratwursts
catalog.notes: IP saute 2tbsp butter, brown brats, 8+10.

catalog.title: Burritos
catalog.notes: Filling: chicken/beef, beans, rice, cheese.

catalog.title: Chicken pot pie
catalog.notes: Cube/boil 2 medium potatoes. Saute 3c cubed chicken, 3 stalks celery, 4 chopped carrots - set aside. Saute 1/4c butter, 1/2 onion, 1/3c flour, 1/2tsp salt, 1/2tsp dry sage or thyme, 1/8tsp pepper. Stir in 2c chicken broth, 3/4c milk, cook until thick and bubbly. Combine all in 9x13 glass dish. Mixing bowl: 1c flour, 1/2tsp salt. With pastry blender, cut in 1/3c shortening until small even pieces. Add enough cold water to just moisten evenly while tossing with a fork. Form a ball, roll out on a lightly floured surface until it fits pie. Roll gently back into rolling pin to lift onto pie. Cut slits for steam to escape. Bake 400º for 15 or until golden brown.

catalog.title: Chicken and dumplings
catalog.notes: TRY poached chicken: boil water/broth, bay leaf, jarlic, lemon, then add chicken breast, remove from heat, cover, let sit 30 minutes; shred. Dumplings: mix 1c flour, 1.5tsp baking powder, 1/2tsp salt, 1tsp parsley. Add 1 egg, 1/2c milk, 2tsbp vegetable oil. Drop by spoonful into boiling chicken broth. Cover and simmer 10-12 minutes. (usually a double batch). Add chicken. Veggies: carrots, peas, green beans, celery, etc.

catalog.title: Pizza
catalog.notes: Start process around 3pm. In bread maker (double-check paddle fitting): 1c water, 1tbsp butter, 2tbsp sugar, 1tsp salt, 2 3/4c packed flour: volcano w/ crater, 1tbsp yeast, mode 8. When done, put oven to highest setting and pizza stone on lowest rack setting. Roll out dough, roll crust over halved cheese sticks. Nummyness sauce: butter, egg, garlic powder -- on crust. Add red sauce, oregano, basil, shredded mozarella cheese, toppings (chicken, onion, etc). Cook 8 minutes, plus 4 with oven off/open.

catalog.title: Salmon and zuquinoa
catalog.notes: 4x Costco marinated salmon from frozen, sous vide 129º for 90 minutes. Rinse 2c quinoa, add to IP, 2c water, stir, add shredded zucchini (3 large or 4 small). 5+10.

catalog.title: Beef tacos
catalog.notes: Saute beef, add taco seasoning. Hard shell tacos, tortillas, refried beans, Greek yogurt, shredded cheddar cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, taco sauce.

catalog.title: Crab Bisque
catalog.notes: IP sauté 3tbsp butter, add 2 diced onions (or scallions), jarlic, 3 diced celery stalks, salt, pepper, 2tsp old bay. Add 2tbsp tomato paste, stir. Add 3tbsp flour, stir. Deglaze with 6c chicken stock and 1c dry white wine. Add 2-3 (finely) diced potatoes and 1 bay leaf. Sauté low until potatoes softened, stirring frequently. Add 1lb (half of large package) crab meat (smooshed/diced), 1/2c heavy cream, and 1 bag peas.

catalog.title: Turkey Cabbage Soup
catalog.notes: Sauté 3lb turkey in 3x 1lb batches (until pink gone, drain liquid, keep browning with salt/pepper/gPowder+oil, transfer and completely deglaze between batches). Sauté 2 onions+jarlic, 2tbsp Worcestershire, paprika, salt/pepper/gPowder. 8c stock, turkey, 3/4 cabbage (1/4" wide chunks); stir. 2c rinsed white rice, 1can crushed tomatoes, 1can diced tomatoes (fire/petite optional); don't stir. IP soup function 4+5. Stir, add 1 handful of each mozarella and Parmesan. Spinach optional. Makes full instant pot.

catalog.title: Green Chile Chicken Enchiladas
catalog.notes: Season 3x large chicken breast, IP saute, set aside, onions, deglaze, 1/2c water, 1c stock (or vice versa), 6+10 (ALTERNATIVELY: grill chicken, and prepare 1c stock). In 2c measuring glass, melt 1/2 stick butter, then add 1/4 flour, stir, then add to IP liquid (stock), stir, add 1 can chopped green chiles, 1tsp cumin, shredded Mexican cheese to desired consistency. Assemble enchiladas with tortillas, diced chicken, black beans, diced tomatoes, cheese. Top with green chili sauce, tomatoes, cheese; broil. Add cilantro on top, greek yogurt on side.

catalog.title: Mongolian Beef
catalog.notes: 2-2.5x recipe. Can add carrots/peppers to beef. Steamed/roasted broccoli on side.

catalog.title: Chicken Dijon
catalog.notes: Chicken breast, mayo/dijon 3:1, bread crumbs

catalog.title: IP chicken alfredo
catalog.notes: Saute/steam veggies, i.e. asparagus, spinach, peppers, broccoli, etc; set aside. Saute family pack of seasoned chicken breast (garlic, salt, pepper, paprika); set aside. Saute diced onions; drain excess oil; deglaze. Add noodles (i.e. small shells), 4c water, trivet+chicken; 5+5. Remove/dice/add chicken, veggies (+halved cherry tomatoes), alfredo sauce; stir.

catalog.title: Chili and rice
catalog.notes: 1 can chili per 1.5c uncooked rice. Add cheese and diced raw onions.

catalog.title: Vegetarian Stuffed Shells
catalog.notes: Boil 1.5 boxes jumbo shells. Saute garlic, 3 bags of spinach. Mix with large container of ricotta, 1c parmesan, 2-3c shredded mozz cheese. Put in 2 large foil pans: sauce, shells, sauce, parmesan sprinkle. Heat in oven.

catalog.title: White Chili
catalog.notes: Saute onion/garlic. Add chicken broth, white beans (big and little, one can of each, not drained), salt, pepper, chopped green chilies, rotisserie chicken, frozen corn, a few teaspoons of cumin, a few tablespoons of cilantro. Simmer in crock pot. Rice optional.

catalog.title: Macaroni salad
catalog.notes: Add rotisserie chicken.
